text: Andreas Charalambous (born 26 July 2001) is a Cypriot sports shooter. He competed in the 10m Air Rifle event at the 2019 Games of the Small States of Europe, where he took the silver medal.(Greek) ==External links== * ==References== Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:Cypriot male sport shooters Category:Sportspeople from Limassol
